descr: "Describes the event of a patient being administered a vaccination or a record of a vaccination as reported by a patient, a clinician or another party and may include vaccine reaction information and what vaccination protocol was followed."

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "Contains the description about the protocol under which the vaccine was administered."

fields.name: authority
fields.descr: "Indicates the authority who published the protocol.  E.g. ACIP."

fields.name: series
fields.descr: "One possible path to achieve presumed immunity against a disease - within the context of an authority."

fields.name: seriesDoses
fields.descr: "The recommended number of doses to achieve immunity."

fields.name: doseStatus
fields.descr: "Indicates if the immunization event should \"count\" against  the protocol."

fields.name: doseStatusReason
fields.descr: "Provides an explanation as to why an immunization event should or should not count against the protocol."
